	<item>
		<title>Lead-Safe Home Projects Workshop</title>
		<link>http://northportlandtoollibrary.org/events/diy-weatherization-workshop/</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 29 Oct 2016 18:25:43 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[NPTL]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Events]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://northportlandtoollibrary.org/?p=869</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<p>Community Energy Project and North Portland Tool Library are excited to provide a free Lead-Safe Home Projects Workshop Wednesday November 16th 6:30-8:00PM at the Kenton Firehouse 2209 N Schofield. Before scraping, sanding, or remodeling any painted surface in pre-1978 housing, check out this class! It&#8217;s great for people who want to do a small project &#8230; <a href="http://northportlandtoollibrary.org/events/diy-weatherization-workshop/" class="more-link">Continue reading <span class="screen-reader-text">Lead-Safe Home Projects Workshop</span> <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a></p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://northportlandtoollibrary.org/events/diy-weatherization-workshop/">Lead-Safe Home Projects Workshop</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://northportlandtoollibrary.org">North Portland Tool Library</a>.</p>
]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://northportlandtoollibrary.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/drawer-e1477765454192.jpg"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-878" src="http://northportlandtoollibrary.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/drawer-e1477765454192-225x300.jpg" alt="drawer" width="172" height="229" srcset="http://northportlandtoollibrary.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/drawer-e1477765454192-225x300.jpg 225w, http://northportlandtoollibrary.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/drawer-e1477765454192.jpg 720w" sizes="(max-width: 172px) 100vw, 172px" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Community Energy Project and North Portland Tool Library are excited to provide a <strong>free</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Lead-Safe Home Projects Workshop<br />
Wednesday November 16th 6:30-8:00PM</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">at the Kenton Firehouse 2209 N Schofield.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Before scraping, sanding, or remodeling any painted surface in pre-1978 housing, check out this class! It&#8217;s great for people who want to do a small project that may involve exposure to lead paint, such as sanding down an old window frame or a reused door with potential lead paint, or a small renovation project in an older home. The class will also discuss the requirements for hiring certified contractors to work on pre-1978 housing. Eligible participants will receive a free kit of testing and working materials, as well as valuable information on protecting your family from lead exposure during home renovations.</p>
<p>This basic class is great for p<span class="text_exposed_show">eople who want to do a small project that may involve exposure to lead paint, such as sanding down an old window frame or a reused door with potential lead paint.<br />
Basic background on history and uses of lead<br />
Project planning and preparation<br />
Lead-Safe work techniques<br />
Project cleanup and dust testing of area<br />
Connections to related resources<br />
The kit for qualified participants includes a starter kit for lead-safe work practices and testing materials, as well as the opportunity borrow a HEPA vacuum.</span></p>
<p>Interested? To guarantee we bring enough materials for all, please register online at:<br />
￼￼￼￼<br />
<a href="http://www.communityenergyproject.org/get-involved/calendar/">www.communityenergyproject.org/get-involved/calendar </a><br />
Or call 503-284-6827 ext 108</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://northportlandtoollibrary.org/events/diy-weatherization-workshop/">Lead-Safe Home Projects Workshop</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://northportlandtoollibrary.org">North Portland Tool Library</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
